heaviest_rainfall.status: Ranked 7th for total rainfall, today's storm had precipitation totalling 23.86mm, falling at 8.3mm per hour at times during the 31.0 hour long storm.  Record-breaking rain fell on 09 November 2025 with a total accumulation of 47.89mm over 144.8 hours and falling at a rate of 24.6mm per hour at times.

heaviest_rainrate.status: 27.6mm per hour was the peak rain rate recorded today ranking 2nd in our overall records.  The storm lasted 2.6 hours and 6.1mm of rain fell.  The rain rate reached 34.3mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.

longest_rain.status: The storm today ranked 7th for the length of the storm when compared to others in our records and it lasted 31.0 hours.  23.86mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 8.3mm per hour.  Rain fell for 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 47.89mm with a maximum intensity of 24.6mm per hour.
